a <- select_if(Assignment_VBA, is.numeric)
options(scipen = 15)
boxplot(na.omit(a$`Duration (in seconds)`))

boxplot(na.omit(a$`USD-2014 Base`),na.omit(a$`USD - 2015 Base`))

boxplot(na.omit(a$`USD Actual Annual Bonus`),na.omit(a$`USD Maximum Annual Bonus`))

Continuous Variable analysis

histograms and Density graph

ggplot(data=Assignment_VBA, aes(Assignment_VBA$`USD-2014 Base`)) + 
  geom_histogram(col="red", 
                 fill="green", 
                 alpha = .2) + 
  geom_density(col=20) + 
  labs(title="Histogram for USD-2014 Base") +
  labs(x="USD", y="Count")

ggplot(data=Assignment_VBA, aes(Assignment_VBA$`USD-2014 Base`)) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(y =..density..),
                 col="red", 
                 fill="green", 
                 alpha = .2) + 
  geom_density(aes(y =..scaled..), col=20) + 
  labs(title="Histogram for USD-2014 Base") +
  labs(x="USD", y="Density")

ggplot(data=Assignment_VBA, aes(Assignment_VBA$`USD - 2015 Base`)) + 
  geom_histogram(col="red", 
                 fill="green", 
                 alpha = .2) + 
  geom_density(col=20) + 
  labs(title="Histogram for USD-2015 Base") +
  labs(x="USD", y="Count")

ggplot(data=Assignment_VBA, aes(Assignment_VBA$`USD - 2015 Base`)) + 
  geom_histogram(aes(y =..density..),
                 col="red",

Bivariate analysis

temp <- (Assignment_VBA[,c(3,4,6,7,10,11,30)])
temp <- setNames(temp, c("14_base","15_base","Bonus", "Max Bonus", "YOCB Finance", "YOCB Legal", "Duration"))
ggcorr(temp, hjust=0.69, nbreaks= 5, label=TRUE, label_size = 4 )

categorical varialble

Position of the respondent

fre <- Assignment_VBA %>% 
  group_by(Position) %>% 
  summarise(counts=n())
fre
ggplot(fre, aes(x= Position, y= counts))+
  geom_bar(fill="#0073c2FF", stat ="Identity", width = 0.4)+
  geom_text(aes(label=counts), vjust= -0.3)+
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold", color="#993333", 
                           size=6),
          axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", color="#993333", 
                           size=10 ))

Occupation Type

fre <- Assignment_VBA %>% 
  group_by(`Ocupation Type`) %>% 
  summarise(counts=n())
fre[,2] <- setNames(fre[,2],"P/P pension")
fre
ggplot(fre, aes(x= `Ocupation Type`, y= counts))+
  geom_bar(fill="#0073c2FF", stat ="Identity", width = 0.4)+
  geom_text(aes(label=counts), vjust= -0.3)+
